{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\nouicompat{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Arial;}{\f1\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}{\f2\fnil\fcharset0 Courier New;}{\f3\fnil\fcharset0 Devanagari Sangam MN;}{\f4\fnil\fcharset0 PingFang SC;}{\f5\fnil\fcharset0 Geeza Pro;}{\f6\fnil\fcharset0 Hiragino Sans;}}{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;\red17\green17\blue17;\red102\green102\blue102;\red232\green30\blue30;\red30\green142\blue62;\red255\green153\blue0;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\sa120\f0\fs22\b\fs36 Amazon Pay - Mathematical Specifications\b0\fs22\par\par\b 1. Refund constraints\b0\parFor a captured transaction with amount A and refunds R_1, R_2, ..., R_n issued over time:\par\par    \u931?\u7522? R\u7522? \u8804? A     (cumulative refunds cannot exceed captured)\par    \u916?A = A \u8722? \u931?\u7522? R\u7522? \u8805? 0   (net captured remains non-negative)\par    R\u7522? > 0 for all i  (refunds are strictly positive)\par\par\b 2. Authorize-to-capture window\b0\parLet t_auth be the authorize timestamp and t_cap the capture timestamp:\par    t_cap \u8722? t_auth \u8804? 7 days   (capture window)\par    otherwise the authorization expires and t_cap is rejected\par\par\b 3. Refund window\b0\parWith t_cap as capture and t_ref as refund:\par    0 < t_ref \u8722? t_cap \u8804? 180 days\par\par\b 4. Latency SLA\b0\parAuthorize-call latency L (ms) must satisfy:\par    P(L \u8804? 5000) \u8805? 0.95   (p95 SLA)\par    P(L \u8804? 8000) \u8805? 0.99   (p99 SLA)\par\par\b 5. FX conversion\b0\parCross-currency capture amount A_settle in merchant's currency:\par    A_settle = A_capture \u215? FX_mid \u215? (1 + spread)\par    where spread \u8776? 0.01 (1 % above mid-market)\par\par\b 6. Webhook retry schedule\b0\parFor the kth retry attempt (k = 1, 2, ..., 6):\par    delay_k = min(2^k \u215? 30s, 4h)  (exponential backoff, capped)\par    total deliverable window = \u931?_\{k=1..6\} delay_k \u8776? 24h\par}